      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Improve Control UI overview hierarchy",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Rework the connected Overview page into an operator-first dashboard with a compact summary strip, Attention, Recent Sessions, Codex Usage, Cron, connector/skill health, and log/event anomaly surfaces above the fold.\n- Preserve the existing Gateway Access and Snapshot cards for disconnected/first-run flows, then demote them below operational content once connected.\n- Keep the layout data-driven from existing gateway/session/cron/auth/log state with fallbacks for api-key-only auth, missing quota data, no sessions, no cron jobs, and unavailable logs.\n\n## Review fixes\n- Restores digit-run blurring for connected Overview recent-session names and adds a regression fixture for a numeric iMessage-style direct-session identifier.\n- Routes the new operator-dashboard user-facing copy through Control UI i18n keys and syncs shipped locale bundles/metadata.\n- Tightens the first-screen layout by capping Attention/Recent Sessions rows and making Codex Usage a compact metric grid.\n\n## Validation\n- `npm test -- src/ui/views/overview.render.test.ts`\n- `npm test -- src/ui/app-render.helpers.node.test.ts`\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:sync`\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\n- `npm run build`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Connected Control UI Overview should show the compact operator dashboard while preserving privacy for recent-session identifiers and avoiding unbounded first-screen card height.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local working OpenClaw Gateway at `http://127.0.0.1:18789/`, serving the built Control UI bundle installed into `/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/control-ui/`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Built the Control UI, copied `dist/control-ui` into the installed OpenClaw Control UI bundle, opened the connected Overview with Playwright, waited for the connected dashboard, redacted private text in the DOM, and captured a screenshot.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the after-fix connected Playwright probe:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servedBundle\": [\n    \"assets/index-XbGp5kf4.js\",\n    \"assets/index-gsqcnrNa.css\"\n  ],\n  \"hasOverview\": true,\n  \"recentRows\": 3,\n  \"moreButtons\": [\n    \"6 more sessions\"\n  ],\n  \"usageNote\": \"Codex 5h window resets 2m.\",\n  \"redactedScreenshotCaptured\": \"tmp/openclaw-overview-pr-proof-redacted.png\"\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The connected Overview rendered the operator dashboard, Recent Sessions was capped to 3 visible rows with a `6 more sessions` footer, Codex Usage rendered as a compact metric grid, and a redacted screenshot was captured after replacing private identifiers before capture.\n- **What was not tested:** No additional gaps for this review pass; broader cross-browser visual QA remains ordinary maintainer review scope.\n\n## Implementation notes\n- This PR intentionally avoids new Gateway RPCs. Message queue state, update posture, and host-health exceptions are represented only when existing dashboard data can support them.\n- Follow-up telemetry could make the dashboard stronger by exposing pending sends/retries, installed-vs-latest version, restart-needed state, and host capacity alerts directly.\n",
